<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "3A">
<servcat sctnbr = "03" scnbr = "01">
<configtype typenbr = "1">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A3116009" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Front Wheel Hub, Steering Knuckle and Wheel Bearing Removal and Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A3116007">Front Wheel Hub and Steering Knuckle Components:Front</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
If the steering knuckle is not removed and installed carefully, the drive shaft dust cover and brake dust cover may damage the dust boots of the suspension arm joints.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
When removing and installing the steering knuckle assembly, be careful not to damage the suspension arm joint dust boots.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A3116009001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Hoist vehicle and remove front wheel. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove drive shaft nut. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A3116003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove brake disc. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A4206005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Pull out wheel hub (1) using special tools.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Outer side of wheel bearing inner race comes out together with wheel hub.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A114">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09943-17912">
09943–17912
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A115">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09942-15511">
09942–15511
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A311011.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.180mm" ver = "02" gw = "193" gh = "123"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect tie-rod end from steering knuckle. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6306003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove front wheel speed sensor from steering knuckle. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A4606007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove strut bracket nuts and bolts. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2206003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect suspension arm joint from steering knuckle. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2206008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering knuckle from drive shaft.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Undo caulking with chisel or the like.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove front brake dust cover (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B311024.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "44.800mm" ver = "01" gw = "114" gh = "110"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove circlip (1) from steering knuckle.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A311016.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "59.096mm" ver = "02" gw = "119" gh = "151"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Using hydraulic press (1) and special tools, push out wheel bearing.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A116">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-75510">
09913–75510
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A117">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09943-37910">
09943–37910
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B311025.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "41.110mm" ver = "01" gw = "92" gh = "100"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Pry wheel bearing outside inner race (1) a little using chisel or the like.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove wheel bearing outside inner race (1) from wheel hub using special tools as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A118">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-65810">
09913–65810
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A119">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-85230">
09913–85230
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7RW01220005.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "80.422mm" ver = "01" gw = "106" gh = "211"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove hub bolts (1) with hydraulic press, if necessary.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
Removing the hub bolts will break the rotation preventing projections on the hub bolts.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Avoid removing the hub bolts unless their replacement is absolutely necessary. If the hub bolts are removed, never reuse the bolts. Replace them with new bolts.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A311012.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "58.536mm" ver = "03" gw = "140" gh = "149"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A3116009002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Insert new hub bolts (1) in hub holes, if removed. Rotate hub bolts slowly to assure that serrations are aligned with those made by original bolts.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I6RS0C220009.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "51.668mm" ver = "01" gw = "170" gh = "130"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Put new wheel bearing (1) on steering knuckle (2) with its brown seal (3) side facing down as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
The used wheel bearing may not operate properly.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Whenever the wheel hub is removed, replace the wheel bearing with a new one.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Press-fit wheel bearing into steering knuckle (2) using special tools as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A120">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09924-74510">
09924–74510
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A121">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09944-78220">
09944–78220
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A122">
<s-part>
(C)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09925-14520">
09925–14520
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A311015.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "71.587mm" ver = "01" gw = "232" gh = "186"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install new circlip (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A311016.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "59.096mm" ver = "02" gw = "119" gh = "151"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set new front brake dust cover.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
The dust cover can easily get deformed.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Be careful when driving the dust cover onto the knuckle.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
If the dust cover is reused, the dust cover can come off and cause the damage of the brake system.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Be sure to install new dust cover.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention4>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install front brake dust cover so that dimensions “a” and “b” become equal as shown in the figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01220038.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "50.196mm" ver = "01" gw = "124" gh = "125"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Caulk more than 4 places with a small cold chisel.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01220039.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.661mm" ver = "01" gw = "166" gh = "104"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Using special tools and hydraulic press, press-fit wheel hub (1) into wheel bearing (2).
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A123">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-75510">
09913–75510
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A124">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09944-78220">
09944–78220
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A311014.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "55.449mm" ver = "02" gw = "209" gh = "141"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install steering knuckle to drive shaft.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect steering knuckle to suspension arm. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2206008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install strut bracket bolts and nuts. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2206003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install front wheel speed sensor. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A4606007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect tie-rod end to steering knuckle. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6306003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install brake disc and brake caliper. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A4206005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten new drive shaft nut. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A3116003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install front wheel. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Confirm front wheel alignment. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2206001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
